title: Should we envoke the "Naaptime" spell?
body:
Aauthor:  ~ 🐙Musashi13#5579 ~ gotchi#928
Discord Thread: https://discord.gg/QeUR3PBg

Summary: We have all had some time to experience the burden of lost time due to our current model for petting our Aavegotchis once every 12 hours. Some of us lost sleep. Some lost kinship. Some set up bots :-o A similar proposal has been made to solve this issue and can be found here:
 https://snapshot.org/#/aavegotchi.eth/proposal/QmQoVWWmABvivkcyh1mGN2d3tcu3j4hpTrHi7uvVrToWDw

I would like to thank Pouis#8690 for that proposal and also offer another possible solution with this goal: to make it easier to pet our Gotchis while also still allowing for an heir of competitiveness to be played out. 

Plaan Aa: Envoke "Naaptime" (11.5 HR pet/24 HR clock/1 HR Naaptime)
Pet Gotchis once every 11.5 hours per 24 hour time period with a 1 hour grace period per 24 hours we call "Naaptime". I personally think this mechanism could solve petting issues with lost time while also still allowing some competitiveness in the kinship aarena.

Plaan B: Envoke "Naaptime" (12 HR pet/25 HR clock/1 HR Naaptime)
Pet Gotchis once every 12 hours per 25 hours with a 1 hour grace period per 25 hours we call "Naaptime". The timing mechanism here should be thought through as it could potentially pose similar issues. But it would allow for a small amount of wiggle room while also still allowing competitiveness by allowing you to get behind in your petting schedule.
choices: Leave as is. I Made a bot anyway
